.TH KULA 1 "February 2026" "kula" "User Manuals"
.SH NAME
kula \- lightweight system monitoring daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kula
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fICOMMAND\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B kula
(Kula-Szpiegula) is a fast, lightweight system monitoring daemon written in Go.
It collects system metrics (CPU, memory, disk, network) and provides a web interface
and a local terminal UI (TUI) for visualization.
.SH COMMANDS
If no command is specified, \fBserve\fR is used by default.
.TP
.B serve
Starts the data collection daemon and web server.
.TP
.B tui
Starts the local Terminal User Interface (TUI) monitor.
.TP
.B hash-password
Generates a bcrypt hash of a password, suitable for use in the configuration file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-config\fR \fCFILE\fP
Path to the configuration file (default: config.yaml).
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR
Show the help message and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/kula/config.yaml
Default system-wide configuration file.
.TP
.I /var/lib/kula
Default directory for persistent data storage.
